Rework pVCF output file splitting (#4)

* Generate well-formed pVCF output files, by internalizing concatenation of BGZF-compressed parts with header & EOF
* Take --split-bed to guide how output files are split (default: one per contig)
* Update to GenomicSQLite v0.9.4

make JointFiles robust to Spark speculative execution

Use GenomicSQLite for VCF records and Variants (#2)

Use GenomicSQLite instead of Spark SQL to store and range-join the [g]VCF records and discovered Variants. This improves Spark app efficiency & reliability, by reducing (i) materialized copying of the VCF records and (ii) spikes in the size of the in-memory working set. (We're still leveraging Spark extensively, to parallelize everything and perform final assembly of the pVCF output records.)
dxapplet: don't delete input VCFs from HDFS

option to allow duplicate samples across callsets (choosing one arbitrarily)
multi spark workers per NUMA node

Write pVCF shards as BGZF instead of Snappy intermediate

Allows much faster concatenation instead of recompression to generate final project vcf.gz. Based on open-source code from GLOW and Hadoop-BAM.

replace most Dataset usage with DataFrame

With "manual" Row de/serialization through the Spark Java API, we reduce our dependence on kotlin-spark-api and we have better control over JVM object instantiation (=> improved performance & memory usage).
